Commands for managing Frappe sites in the current project.

Examples:
  weg site list              # List all sites
  weg site new <name>        # Create a new site
  weg site drop <name>       # Delete a site
  weg site use <name>        # Set default site

Usage:
  weg site [command]

Available Commands:
  backup      Backup a Frappe site
  browse      Open site in browser with auto-login
  config      Manage site configuration
  drop        Delete a site
  hosts       Manage /etc/hosts entries for sites
  install     Install an app on a site
  list        List all sites
  maintenance Manage site maintenance mode
  new         Create a new site
  password    Set or reset a user password
  restore     Restore a Frappe site from backup
  use         Set the default site

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for site

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg site [command] --help" for more information about a command.
